I would like to know if there is an add-on that would automatically add Melbourne (or Australian) public holidays into the calender function in the JIRA Service Desk Customer Portal (SLA --> Calendar --> Holidays).
As public holidays such as Good Friday, East Monday and Melbourne Cup Day all fall on different dates each year, I would like to be able to simply import a file into the JIRA Service Desk Calendar that would automatically enter the public holidays.
Without this I would have to manually enter public holidays and with many many service desk customer portals for many different clients this would be very time consuming.

