Certain types of issues can require a specific set of steps to handle. For example, responding with a workaround, setting a label and transitioning the issue.

When an agent encounters these types of issue frequently, he/she would need to repeat these steps numerous times. This can be error prone and frustrating.

It may be useful to provide a way to define 'quick actions' that an agent can trigger to perform a pre-defined set of steps for the issue in question.

